Title: Optical Communication for Pointer Based Algorithms  
Author: Richard J. Anderson Gary L. Miller 
Note: (Extended Abstract)  
Abstract: In this paper we study the Local Memory P-RAM. This model allows unit cost communication but assumes that the shared memory is divided into modules. This model is motivated by a consideration of potential optical computers. We show that fundamental problems such as list-ranking and parallel tree contraction can be implemented on this model in O(log n) time using n= log n processors. To solve the list-ranking problem we introduce a general asynchronous technique which has relevance to a number of problems.
